 * \section intro_sec High Concept

Room Furniture Planner is a game designed to work as a platform for companies which sell furniture to provide an interface for their clients to visualize their ideas for interior design of their homes with the furniture that the company sells. The interface is step-by-step so that it is not overwhelming the users with information. It provides users with the opportunity to visualize what they are going to receive from the company when they order from them. It is meant to be integrated within a website.

It has a clean material design. There is a menu with options for each object which pops out from the object itself and stays within proximity of it. The design shows guides the user to what the next step is.

1.
1) **First we create rooms:**

Here the user has the opportunity to create the layout of the rooms they are interested in planning the furniture for.

1. 2) **Then we put funriture in the rooms:**

Here the user has the opportunity to put furniture in the rooms that they have created and position it.

1. 3) **Then we put decoration in the rooms:**

Here the user has the opportunity to put decoration in the rooms that they have created and position it.

# Menu

The menu is the area where new items to add can be found. It provides a navigation on the top, in the header. It is positioned on the left of the screen.

## Animations

### Animation of the opening

The "+" button expands and changes its color to that of the header of the menu area with the Material design&#39;s ripple effect: the circle expands until it covers the opacity mask of the menu&#39;s header and the color shifting uses the ripple effect as well. A &quot;wave&quot; with the color of the header is spawned at the point where the user has pressed the button which expands until the boundaries of the button. As a result, there are two ripples which travel at the same speed. After the header&#39;s opacity mask is fully revealed, it is positioned halfway through to the top of the screen (its destination) when the rest of the menu area starts expanding from the header.

